Create active task folders under `tasks/todo/` with the format `YYYY-MM-DD-description/`.

Quick-start summary:
- use one active task folder per effort;
- keep `task_plan.md`, `findings.md`, and `progress.md` current throughout the session;
- move completed tasks to `tasks/archive/` with the same folder name.

Each active task folder should contain:
- `task_plan.md`
- `findings.md`
- `progress.md`
- optionally `mechanism_table.md`, `orchestrator_prompt.md`, and `orchestrator-log.jsonl` for YES/NO-gated orchestration campaigns

Source of truth:
- detailed workflow and policy rules live in `AGENTS.md`;
- detailed repo layout and module ownership notes live in `docs/architecture.md`;
- adjacent planning surfaces (`TODO.md`, `implementation_notes.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `Bugs.md`) must stay synchronized when relevant;
- a repo-local top-level `orchestrator/` (when present) is a separate successor control plane for repo-wide round execution; runtime roadmap files are resolved from `orchestrator/state.json` via `roadmap_dir`, not from the top-level roadmap stubs;
- root-level `task_plan.md`, `findings.md`, and `progress.md` are historical artifacts, not the current active-task workflow.
